M a l e: Protarsomeres 1 to 3 weakly widened. Aedeagus (
Figs 110, 111
) 0.35-0.42 mm long, symmetrical, weakly sclerotized. Median lobe with flattened basal bulb, small, hardly prominent articular processes and long apical process. Latter almost in axis with basal bulb, shortly curved near blunt apex. Parameres lacking membranous lobes, weakly curved in dorsal and lateral views. Internal sac with two narrow rods and spine-like structures distinct in its middle part, in dorsal view.
